    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve factors meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieved level 2 against a required level 3; this shortfall is accepted given that ASTM F1717 is a standardized ambient-condition test and the regulatory context does not require in-vivo environmental simulation for static mechanical characterization. All three QoIs pass quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, relative error < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is judged credible for the stated COU.",
